The species is most likely of Western Palaearctic origin, but has an almost cosmopolitan distribution today. Outside the Palaearctic region, it has been introduced in the Australian region (
New Zealand
), as well as in South America (
Colombia
) and North America (
ASSING & WUNDERLE 1995
); recently it was also reported from 
South Africa
for the first time (
NEWTON 2006
).
